"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Concepts\\n\\n`dgov` is built on a set of core engineering principles designed to make multi-agent orchestration as predictable as a compiler.\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\n| Module | Role |\\n|--------|------|\\n| `kernel.py` | Pure `(state, event) → (new_state, actions)` — no I/O |\\n| `runner.py` | Async DAG executor feeding the kernel |\\n| `worker.py` | Standalone OpenAI-client subprocess |\\n| `settlement.py` | ruff auto-fix + lint gate + sentrux policy gate |\\n| `worktree.py` | Git worktree create/merge/remove |\\n| `plan.py` | TOML plan parsing, DAG compilation |\\n| `persistence/` | SQLite event store (panes + events + slug history) |\\n\\n## Deterministic Kernel\\n\\nThe heart of `dgov` is a pure state machine. It doesn't know about the network, the filesystem, or LLMs. It only knows how to transition state based on events (like `TaskDone` or `TaskFailed`) and emit actions (like `MergeTask` or `RetryTask`).\\n\\nThis separation makes the orchestration logic perfectly testable and resilient to process crashes.\\n\\n## Snapshot Isolation\\n\\nEvery task dispatched by `dgov` runs in its own **git worktree**. \\n- **Isolated Environment**: Workers cannot accidentally interfere with each other's files.\\n- **Commit-or-Kill**: Changes are only merged back to the main branch if they pass all settlement gates (linting, tests, and architectural checks).\\n- **Audit Trail**: Every attempt is a branch. You can always inspect exactly what a worker was doing by checking its worktree.\\n\\n## Settlement Layer\\n\\nThe settlement layer acts as a automated PR review. Before any code is merged, `dgov` performs:\\n1. **Autofix**: Running formatters and simple lint fixes.\\n2. **Review**: Fast sanity checks (e.g. no secrets, no binary files).\\n3. **Validation**: Running the project's own test suite and architectural gates.\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/concepts#concepts\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p><code>dgov</code> is built on a set of core engineering principles designed to make multi-agent orchestration as predictable as a compiler.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts.mdx#concepts\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\ndgov is built on a set of core engineering principles designed to make multi-agent orchestration as predictable as a compiler.\\n\",\"title\":\"Concepts\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/concepts#architecture\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Module</th><th>Role</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>kernel.py</code></td><td>Pure <code>(state, event) → (new_state, actions)</code> — no I/O</td></tr><tr><td><code>runner.py</code></td><td>Async DAG executor feeding the kernel</td></tr><tr><td><code>worker.py</code></td><td>Standalone OpenAI-client subprocess</td></tr><tr><td><code>settlement.py</code></td><td>ruff auto-fix + lint gate + sentrux policy gate</td></tr><tr><td><code>worktree.py</code></td><td>Git worktree create/merge/remove</td></tr><tr><td><code>plan.py</code></td><td>TOML plan parsing, DAG compilation</td></tr><tr><td><code>persistence/</code></td><td>SQLite event store (panes + events + slug history)</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts.mdx#architecture\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nModuleRolekernel.pyPure (state, event) → (new_state, actions) — no I/Orunner.pyAsync DAG executor feeding the kernelworker.pyStandalone OpenAI-client subprocesssettlement.pyruff auto-fix + lint gate + sentrux policy gateworktree.pyGit worktree create/merge/removeplan.pyTOML plan parsing, DAG compilationpersistence/SQLite event store (panes + events + slug history)\\n\",\"title\":\"Architecture\",\"titles\":[\"Concepts\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts#deterministic-kernel\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The heart of <code>dgov</code> is a pure state machine. It doesn&#x27;t know about the network, the filesystem, or LLMs. It only knows how to transition state based on events (like <code>TaskDone</code> or <code>TaskFailed</code>) and emit actions (like <code>MergeTask</code> or <code>RetryTask</code>).</p>\\n<p>This separation makes the orchestration logic perfectly testable and resilient to process crashes.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts.mdx#deterministic-kernel\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe heart of dgov is a pure state machine. It doesn&#x27;t know about the network, the filesystem, or LLMs. It only knows how to transition state based on events (like TaskDone or TaskFailed) and emit actions (like MergeTask or RetryTask).\\nThis separation makes the orchestration logic perfectly testable and resilient to process crashes.\\n\",\"title\":\"Deterministic Kernel\",\"titles\":[\"Concepts\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts#snapshot-isolation\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Every task dispatched by <code>dgov</code> runs in its own <strong>git worktree</strong>.</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Isolated Environment</strong>: Workers cannot accidentally interfere with each other&#x27;s files.</li>\\n<li><strong>Commit-or-Kill</strong>: Changes are only merged back to the main branch if they pass all settlement gates (linting, tests, and architectural checks).</li>\\n<li><strong>Audit Trail</strong>: Every attempt is a branch. You can always inspect exactly what a worker was doing by checking its worktree.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts.mdx#snapshot-isolation\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nEvery task dispatched by dgov runs in its own git worktree.\\n\\nIsolated Environment: Workers cannot accidentally interfere with each other&#x27;s files.\\nCommit-or-Kill: Changes are only merged back to the main branch if they pass all settlement gates (linting, tests, and architectural checks).\\nAudit Trail: Every attempt is a branch. You can always inspect exactly what a worker was doing by checking its worktree.\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Snapshot Isolation\",\"titles\":[\"Concepts\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts#settlement-layer\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The settlement layer acts as a automated PR review. Before any code is merged, <code>dgov</code> performs:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Autofix</strong>: Running formatters and simple lint fixes.</li>\\n<li><strong>Review</strong>: Fast sanity checks (e.g. no secrets, no binary files).</li>\\n<li><strong>Validation</strong>: Running the project&#x27;s own test suite and architectural gates.</li>\\n</ol>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts.mdx#settlement-layer\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe settlement layer acts as a automated PR review. Before any code is merged, dgov performs:\\n\\nAutofix: Running formatters and simple lint fixes.\\nReview: Fast sanity checks (e.g. no secrets, no binary files).\\nValidation: Running the project&#x27;s own test suite and architectural gates.\\n\",\"title\":\"Settlement Layer\",\"titles\":[\"Concepts\"]}]}}"
